http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.value: A broad term to describe all mineral tenement areas that are undergoing an application process.
TAS - Tenement cancelled. eg, for non-payment of rent on granted tenement
TAS - Application was declined as requirements for application assessment were not satisfied.
TAS - End of term granted tenement or tenement converted to another
Areas under moratorium prior to being released for EL application
TAS - Tenement forfeited under Mining Act 1929
A mineral tenement has been granted and is current.
TAS - Lease cancelled subject to appeal for reinstatement.

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#pref.value: granted (cancelled subject to appeal for reinstatement)

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.value: TAS - Tenement subject to appeal before the Mining Tribunal.

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#pref.value: granted (decision to refuse extension of term under appeal)

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.value: TAS - Tenement subject to appeal before the Minister and /or Mining Tribunal.

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#pref.value: granted (decision to revoke subject to or under appeal)

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.value: NT - A classification for amalgamated titles formed from two or more granted titles (usually after significant partial relinquishments)
Tenement grant period has expired
A broad term to describe all non-current, historical mineral tenements.
Tenement application is pending approval. Tenement is not yet granted.
TAS - Part of this area is about to be released as an ERA area balance of area to remain granted.
TAS - Tenement subject to application for renewal
TAS - Tenement undergoing surrender process
TAS - Registered application or renewal refused by Minister
TAS - Revocation of granted tenement
TAS - Voluntary relinquishment of granted tenement
TAS - Applicant withdrew application

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: This concept scheme defines terms used to describe the status of mineral tenements in Australian and New Zealand jurisdictions (eg, granted, application, expired).
